Quote: Roasted peru peru. So named because they were first brough here by Peruvian sailors, peru peru are unusual long-shaped tubers that have a delicious flavour similar to new potatoes, and are marbled with purple to varying degrees inside. You might also see them labelled as <i>urenika</i> potatoes.
